      <p>
      Midata is a new government initiative to give consumers access to the personal data that business's store about them in a machine readable format. Midata will enable new services that give consumer insight into their behavior. emPowerMi is an example application developed at the Midata hackathon to demonstrate how midata can help consumers reduce their energy usage.</p>
      <p>Energy companies will give access to consumer's energy consumption data and details about their property. This data can be used to give consumer insight into how they can reduce their energy bills and their carbon footprint. Using that data we can:
        <ul>
          <li>give an instant summary of how much energy they are using</li>
          <li>suggest a range of energy efficiency measure that may help them</li>
          <li>show the impact of these energy efficiency measures on their bills</li>
        </ul>
      </p>
